          <td colspan="2"><span
class="postbody">Sorry to hear about the 'Zerkers, but all in all this is one hell of a patch.  I would've like to see more high-end loot consistancy rather than low-end loot consistancy, but a new zone is a very welcome addition.  Unfortunately it sounds like one large Escort Mission, and those have never been buggy... 
<br />

<br />
It was smart to roll out Mentoring before the first Adventure Pack.  I'd like to think they did it because they didn't want anyone regardless of level to not purchase it, but hell, Mentoring is too damn cool, so I'll give them the benefit of the doubt  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" />  Now I'm in a pickle, I rolled a Troubador specifically to see all the content I missed, and I like it far more than my ShadowKnight.  If only they allowed us to change class once I'd be set.    <img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="Cool" border="0" /></span><span
class="gensmall"></span></td>
